# Economic Modeling of Container Vessel Cost of Sales
### A Dynamic Tug Towage Cost Simulation for the Port of New York and New Jersey
**Research Analysis by Gemini Deep Research**

---

## 1. Executive Summary
The accurate simulation of **Cost of Sales**—specifically Operating Expenses (OPEX) allocated to port calls—requires microscopic analysis of localized harbor economics. This report deconstructs the towage cost architecture governing **Ocean Network Express (ONE)** and **Moran Towing Corporation** within the Port of New York and New Jersey.

---

## 2. Macroeconomics: Port Omission vs. Speeding
Fleet operators face a binary strategic decision when experiencing operational delays:

| Strategy | Primary Benefits | Economic Penalties |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Port Omission** | Total elimination of port/terminal costs; significant fuel savings; schedule recovery. | Severe degradation of customer delivery reliability; potential contractual penalties. |
| **Speeding** | Preservation of cargo commitments; maintains revenue per TEU and transparency. | Exponential spikes in fuel consumption (cubic function of speed); guaranteed harbor OPEX. |

---

